Pablo Galindo Salgado, the Python 3.10 and 3.11 release manager,
gave this talk on his co-authored [PEP 657](https://peps.python.org/pep-0657/).

One fascinating fact about Pablo
is he received a PhD in theoretical math and physics
before becoming a software engineer.
In general, he's a captivating speaker and his talk shares great perspective.
